Steps taken to install Sass on Windows:

1.  Navigated to the alx-intermediate-frontend repository:
    cd ~/OneDrive/Desktop/alx-intermediate-frontend

2.  Created the project directory:
    mkdir 0x03-sass_scss

3.  Moved into the new directory:
    cd 0x03-sass_scss

4.  Attempted to install sass@3.7.4, which resulted in an ETARGET error (no matching version found):
    npm install sass@3.7.4

5.  Successfully installed the correct global version of Sass (1.77.4):
    npm install -g sass@1.77.4

6.  Verified Sass installation:
    sass --version
    (Output: 1.77.4 compiled with dart2js 3.4.2)